Release procedure:

 * Increase memory
   -> export MAVEN_OPTS="-Xmx512m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m"

 * Prepare for release:
  * Clean everything
    -> mvn clean
  * change the version to a fixed one (for example, if we were to 2.1.0-SNAPSHOT, go to 2.1.0)
    -> cd parent && mvn versions:set -DnewVersion=2.1.0 && cd ..
  * commit and tag the release
    -> hg commit -m "prepare for 2.1.0 release"
    -> hg tag v2.1.0

 * Do the release
  * Compile, install in the local repository and deploy 
    -> mvn deploy
    
 * Increment for development
  * Clean everything
    -> mvn clean
  * change the version (note: it will change the osgi version AND the pom versions)
    -> cd parent && mvn versions:set -DnewVersion=2.2.0-SNAPSHOT && cd ..
  * commit
    -> hg commit -m "increment to 2.2.0 development version"

 * Develop!

